author: psiwebtn
title: On This Date
text:
On This Date Saturday, October 10, 2015 
October 10, 1964 - The Carazo brothers score three of their team’s four touchdowns to help Palmerton defeat Catasauqua, 26-6, in a Lehigh Valley League matchup. Frank Carazo reaches the end zone on runs of one and three yards while his younger brother Steve, filling in at quarterback for the injured Roger Lipics, scores on a one-yard plunge. The Blue Bombers also receive a 60-yard interception return for a touchdown by Gus Guedes. Tom Lloyd’s blocked punt sets up one of the elder Carazo’s scores.
